places.name: Cristo Rei of Dili
places.perex: Cristo Rei of Dili is a 27.0-metre-high statue of Jesus located atop a globe in Dili, East Timor.

places.name: National Stadium
places.perex: National Stadium is a multi-purpose stadium in Dili, East Timor. It is used mostly for association football matches.

places.name: National University of Timor Leste
places.perex: The National University of East Timor, based in the East Timorese capital Dili, is the major institution of higher education in East Timor.

places.name: Tatamailau
places.perex: Tatamailau, or Tata Mailau, sometimes referred as Mount Ramelau, is the highest mountain in East Timor and also of Timor island at 2,986 m.

places.name: Universidade da Paz
places.perex: The Universidade da Paz is a private undergraduate university in Dili, East Timor

places.name: Hotel Dili
places.perex: Hotel Dili is a hotel on the waterfront in Dili, East Timor, established in 1933. It was purchased by Australian Frank Favaro in 1971.

places.name: Motael Church
places.perex: The Church de São António de Motael is the oldest Roman Catholic church in East Timor. It was rebuilt in 1955 in the old Portuguese style.

places.name: Matebian
places.perex: Matebian or Matebean is the third highest mountain in Timor Leste, after Ramelau.

places.name: National Parliament
places.perex: The National Parliament is the unicameral national legislature in East Timor.

places.name: Immaculate Conception Cathedral, Dili
places.perex: The Immaculate Conception Cathedral in Dili is the main church of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Dili, East Timor.

places.name: Palácio de Lahane
places.perex: Palácio de Lahane is an historic building in East Timor.

places.name: Ira Lalaro
places.perex: Lake Ira Lalaro is a waterway in Mehara, Subdistrict Tutuala, Lautém District of East Timor.
